Commentary Text: Ravi Bishnoi to Maxwell, out Lbw!! Big wicket and Ravi Bishnoi is thrilled. Maxwell reverses his stance and misses the reverse-sweep, was the topspinner again, the seam came out horizontal and beautifully, extra bounce and beats Maxwell on the shot, hit on the tummy, given out by the ump. Maxwell reviews but it's just clipping and that will do for Ravi Bishnoi and LSG. Umpire's call working in LSG's favor. Maxwell is not happy though as he curses with an expletive and then leaves. Maxwell lbw b Ravi Bishnoi 4(5)

Commentary Text: Harshal Patel to Gowtham, out Gowtham Run Out!! 1 run completed. A run-out appeal has been referred to the third umpire. Oh he's gone! Gowtham was batting so well, but he's been run out! What a breakthrough! Could well be the game! Good length outside off, Gowtham pushes it through backward point and runs hard. It's tight on the second run with the fielder charging across, but Gowtham risks it. And he pays. That was brilliant from Sonu Yadav who attacked the ball and released a flat throw on the bounce to DK. Gowtham run out (Sonu Yadav/Karthik) 23(13) [4s-1 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Karn Sharma to Pooran, out Caught by Lomror!! This was coming. Right from ball one you could sense that Pooran was here to try and counter attack and had absolutely no intentions of hanging around. He picked the right ball but just didn't get the desired timing. Picked the legbreak from outside leg and got too much height than distance on the slogsweep. Lomror at deep square runs across to his right and puts in a dive to complete the catch. Half the side back in the hut for the home side. Pooran c Lomror b Karn Sharma 9(7) [6s-1]

Commentary Text: Hasaranga to Hooda, out Stumped!! Hooda could believe what he just saw on the big screen. To be fair, he had an air of guilt surrounding him soon as the umpire took it upstairs. He perhaps knew? It was the the gentle legbreak from Hasaranga, managed to beat the prodding blade of Hooda. Beat the outside edge and got the ball to skid at a nice height to DK. Hooda was prodding a little too much and couldn't get his back foot inside in the nick of time. It was just on the line when the bails came off. Hooda st Karthik b Hasaranga 1(2)

Commentary Text: Hazlewood to Ayush Badoni, out Caught by Kohli!! It's Kohli again. He blows a kiss to someone after taking that catch. Hazlewood got Badoni dancing to his tunes in the first over and perhaps got into his head. He switched ends and bowled this a touch fuller than the good length. Badoni's eyes lit up and he didn't bother to press forward, just a slap drive and it has been intercepted by a leaping VK at cover.
